Posting my java two pass solution O(N) .

 - Reimagine the circular array as a linear one by appending the first number to the end.
 - Iterate the array twice from 0 to n-1, and once again from 1 to n, 
 - Return the max count
 - The key is to increment the index 'i' once again if there is a pairing

